@Hamish the claim on temperamental estimates is expected from a technical perspective. We use a minimum logprobs aggregation for the response, which even with temperature fixed to 0 still generates widely varying probability estimates…
We can reduce this variance in follow up work by testing self-consistency approaches and averaging over multiple soft votes.
As I chatted with @Kaustubh (KD) , our confidence estimation needs a major revisit, preferably start of Q3.
